SYNOPSIS
        object clone_unique_object(string name)

DESCRIPTION
        Clones a new object much like the clone_object efun would.
        The difference, however, is that clone_unique_object will
        register the new object with the unique tracking system
        and only allow a single instance of the unique object to
        be in the game at a given time.
        
        Note that the pathname must be complete, which means there 
        are no relative paths allowed.

        NOTE: clone_unique_object will not check if the object in
              question has been cloned before using clone_object.
              Thus, it is entirely possible to clone several instances
              of an object using clone_object and still get a valid
              object from clone_unique_object. However, after a single
              unique object is created, any additional calls to
              clone_unique_object will not produce a new object as long
              as the old object is still in the game.
              
EXAMPLE
        // Clone unique sword
        object sword, sword2;
        sword = clone_unique_object("/obj/sword");
        
        // Following call to clone_unique_object returns 0
        sword2 = clone_unique_object("/obj/sword");
        if(!sword2)
          write("The second sword wasn't cloned!\n");

